––– comment –––
==========================================================================
SECTION A: Content Fields Handling
Tests: single field, two fields, three fields
==========================================================================
––– comment –––
Create a basic model for content fields tests
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "CREATE RAG MODEL fields_assistant (llm_provider='openai', llm_model='gpt-4o-mini');"
––– output –––
+--------------------------------------+
| uuid                                 |
+--------------------------------------+
| #!/[0-9a-z]{8}-[0-9a-z]{4}-[0-9a-z]{4}-[0-9a-z]{4}-[0-9a-z]{12}/!# |
+--------------------------------------+
––– comment –––
Test A1: Single content field — 'content' only
Expected: response based on content text, sources present
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "CALL CONVERSATIONAL_RAG('What is vector search?', 'docs', 'fields_assistant', 'content')\G" | tee /tmp/rag_adv_a1.txt | grep -E "conversation_uuid:|response:|sources:"
––– output –––
conversation_uuid: #!/[a-z0-9-]+/!#
         response: #!/.+/!#
          sources: #!/\[.*/!#
––– comment –––
Test A2: Two content fields — 'title,content'
Expected: sources include both title and content data
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "CALL CONVERSATIONAL_RAG('Tell me about RAG', 'docs', 'fields_assistant', 'title,content')\G" | tee /tmp/rag_adv_a2.txt | grep -E "conversation_uuid:|response:|sources:"
––– output –––
conversation_uuid: #!/[a-z0-9-]+/!#
         response: #!/.+/!#
          sources: #!/\[.*/!#
––– comment –––
Verify A2: sources contain title field data
––– input –––
grep -c '"title"' /tmp/rag_adv_a2.txt
––– output –––
#!/[1-9][0-9]*/!#
––– comment –––
Test A3: Three content fields — 'title,content,category'
Expected: sources include all three fields
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "CALL CONVERSATIONAL_RAG('Explain neural networks', 'docs', 'fields_assistant', 'title,content,category')\G" | tee /tmp/rag_adv_a3.txt | grep -E "conversation_uuid:|response:|sources:"
––– output –––
conversation_uuid: #!/[a-z0-9-]+/!#
         response: #!/.+/!#
          sources: #!/\[.*/!#
––– comment –––
Verify A3: sources contain category field data
––– input –––
grep -c '"category"' /tmp/rag_adv_a3.txt
––– output –––
#!/[1-9][0-9]*/!#
––– comment –––
Cleanup fields_assistant model
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "DROP RAG MODEL fields_assistant;"
––– output –––
––– comment –––
==========================================================================
SECTION B: Style Prompt Effect (soft assertions)
Tests: custom style prompt vs default prompt
==========================================================================
––– comment –––
Test B1: Model with custom pirate style prompt
Expected: model accepts style_prompt and returns valid response (soft check)
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "CREATE RAG MODEL pirate_assistant (llm_provider='openai', llm_model='gpt-4o-mini', style_prompt='You are a pirate. Always respond in pirate speak using words like arr, matey, ye.');"
––– output –––
+--------------------------------------+
| uuid                                 |
+--------------------------------------+
| #!/[0-9a-z]{8}-[0-9a-z]{4}-[0-9a-z]{4}-[0-9a-z]{4}-[0-9a-z]{12}/!# |
+--------------------------------------+
––– comment –––
Verify pirate model has correct style_prompt via DESCRIBE
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "DESCRIBE RAG MODEL pirate_assistant\G" | grep -A1 'style_prompt'
––– output –––
property: style_prompt
   value: #!/.*[Yy]ou are a pirate.*/!#
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "CALL CONVERSATIONAL_RAG('Tell me about Python programming', 'docs', 'pirate_assistant', 'content,title')\G" | tee /tmp/rag_adv_b1.txt | grep -E "conversation_uuid:|response:|sources:"
––– output –––
conversation_uuid: #!/[a-z0-9-]+/!#
         response: #!/.+/!#
          sources: #!/\[.*/!#
––– comment –––
Test B2: Model with default (empty) style prompt
Expected: default behavior, valid response
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "CREATE RAG MODEL default_assistant (llm_provider='openai', llm_model='gpt-4o-mini');"
––– output –––
+--------------------------------------+
| uuid                                 |
+--------------------------------------+
| #!/[0-9a-z]{8}-[0-9a-z]{4}-[0-9a-z]{4}-[0-9a-z]{4}-[0-9a-z]{12}/!# |
+--------------------------------------+
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "CALL CONVERSATIONAL_RAG('Tell me about Python programming', 'docs', 'default_assistant', 'content,title')\G" | tee /tmp/rag_adv_b2.txt | grep -E "conversation_uuid:|response:|sources:"
––– output –––
conversation_uuid: #!/[a-z0-9-]+/!#
         response: #!/.+/!#
          sources: #!/\[.*/!#
––– comment –––
Cleanup style models
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "DROP RAG MODEL pirate_assistant;"
––– output –––
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "DROP RAG MODEL default_assistant;"
––– output –––
––– comment –––
==========================================================================
SECTION C: k_results Parameter
Tests: k_results=1 (single document) vs k_results=5 (multiple documents)
==========================================================================
––– comment –––
Test C1: Model with k_results=1 — should return exactly 1 source document
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "CREATE RAG MODEL single_result_assistant (llm_provider='openai', llm_model='gpt-4o-mini', settings='{\"k_results\":1}');"
––– output –––
+--------------------------------------+
| uuid                                 |
+--------------------------------------+
| #!/[0-9a-z]{8}-[0-9a-z]{4}-[0-9a-z]{4}-[0-9a-z]{4}-[0-9a-z]{12}/!# |
+--------------------------------------+
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "CALL CONVERSATIONAL_RAG('Tell me about AI', 'docs', 'single_result_assistant', 'content,title')\G" | tee /tmp/rag_adv_c1.txt | grep -E "conversation_uuid:|response:|sources:"
––– output –––
conversation_uuid: #!/[a-z0-9-]+/!#
         response: #!/.+/!#
          sources: #!/\[.*/!#
––– comment –––
Verify C1: sources contain exactly 1 document (count "id" occurrences)
––– input –––
grep -o '"id"' /tmp/rag_adv_c1.txt | wc -l | tr -d ' '
––– output –––
1
––– comment –––
Test C2: Model with k_results=5 — should return up to 5 source documents
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "CREATE RAG MODEL multi_result_assistant (llm_provider='openai', llm_model='gpt-4o-mini', settings='{\"k_results\":5}');"
––– output –––
+--------------------------------------+
| uuid                                 |
+--------------------------------------+
| #!/[0-9a-z]{8}-[0-9a-z]{4}-[0-9a-z]{4}-[0-9a-z]{4}-[0-9a-z]{12}/!# |
+--------------------------------------+
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "CALL CONVERSATIONAL_RAG('Tell me about AI', 'docs', 'multi_result_assistant', 'content,title')\G" | tee /tmp/rag_adv_c2.txt | grep -E "conversation_uuid:|response:|sources:"
––– output –––
conversation_uuid: #!/[a-z0-9-]+/!#
         response: #!/.+/!#
          sources: #!/\[.*/!#
––– comment –––
Verify C2: sources contain more than 1 document
––– input –––
grep -o '"id"' /tmp/rag_adv_c2.txt | wc -l | tr -d ' '
––– output –––
#!/[2-9][0-9]*/!#
––– comment –––
Cleanup k_results models
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "DROP RAG MODEL single_result_assistant;"
––– output –––
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "DROP RAG MODEL multi_result_assistant;"
––– output –––
––– comment –––
==========================================================================
SECTION D: Conversation Isolation
Tests: two independent conversations don't share context
==========================================================================
––– comment –––
Create a shared model for isolation tests
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "CREATE RAG MODEL isolation_assistant (llm_provider='openai', llm_model='gpt-4o-mini');"
––– output –––
+--------------------------------------+
| uuid                                 |
+--------------------------------------+
| #!/[0-9a-z]{8}-[0-9a-z]{4}-[0-9a-z]{4}-[0-9a-z]{4}-[0-9a-z]{12}/!# |
+--------------------------------------+
––– comment –––
Test D1: Conversation A — query about AI
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "CALL CONVERSATIONAL_RAG('What is RAG?', 'docs', 'isolation_assistant', 'content,title', 'conv-iso-aaa')\G" | tee /tmp/rag_adv_d1.txt | grep -E "conversation_uuid:|response:|sources:"
––– output –––
conversation_uuid: conv-iso-aaa
         response: #!/.*(RAG|[Rr]etrieval).*/!#
          sources: #!/\[.*/!#
––– comment –––
Verify D1: sources contain AI category
––– input –––
grep -c '"category":"AI"' /tmp/rag_adv_d1.txt
––– output –––
#!/[1-9][0-9]*/!#
––– comment –––
Test D2: Conversation B (different UUID) — query about movies
Expected: no AI context leaks from Conversation A
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "CALL CONVERSATIONAL_RAG('Tell me about TV shows and movies', 'docs', 'isolation_assistant', 'content,title', 'conv-iso-bbb')\G" | tee /tmp/rag_adv_d2.txt | grep -E "conversation_uuid:|response:|sources:"
––– output –––
conversation_uuid: conv-iso-bbb
         response: #!/.+/!#
          sources: #!/\[.*/!#
––– comment –––
Verify D2: sources contain Entertainment category
––– input –––
grep -c '"category":"Entertainment"' /tmp/rag_adv_d2.txt
––– output –––
#!/[1-9][0-9]*/!#
––– comment –––
Cleanup isolation model
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "DROP RAG MODEL isolation_assistant;"
––– output –––
––– comment –––
